SweetPea-Style-Default

The first experimental custom scaffolding style for SweetPea. Works but
experimental, not sure if SweetPea users even want this.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install
	
	-or-
	
	cpan SweetPea::Style::Default;
	
USAGE

	... at the cli (command-line interface)
	perl -MSweetPea::Style::Default -e makeapp
	

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc SweetPea::Style::Default

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=SweetPea-Style-Default

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/SweetPea-Style-Default

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/SweetPea-Style-Default

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/SweetPea-Style-Default/


